00:00:55.050 --> 00:00:59.119
That's when it's important to keep our eyes open and watch out for what can put us in danger.

00:00:59.879 --> 00:01:02.779
Here are seven early signs you may be in a toxic relationship.

00:01:03.960 --> 00:01:07.129
One: Your partner has heavy ex-baggage.

00:01:07.800 --> 00:01:13.700
Timing plays a major factor on relationships that can either make it or break it. If you find yourself constantly

00:01:14.010 --> 00:01:18.319
consoling your partner as they mourn over their ex, then it's a sign they haven't moved on yet.

00:01:18.870 --> 00:01:24.349
They need time to grieve and heal over the loss of their ex before they are ready to enter a relationship again.

00:01:24.810 --> 00:01:26.070
But when you're in love,

00:01:26.070 --> 00:01:33.050
it's easy to get hopeful and become blind to the fact that your partner isn't emotionally invested in you when their heart still belongs elsewhere.

00:01:33.900 --> 00:01:36.319
Ultimately, you'll end up being the one getting hurt.

00:01:37.110 --> 00:01:42.440
Recognize that your role isn't solely to be a shoulder to cry on. You deserve love just like anyone else.

00:01:42.810 --> 00:01:50.330
But you can't receive that if you're busy being someone's rebound. Two: Your partner often lies to you about nearly everything.

00:01:51.090 --> 00:01:55.099
There's no harm in telling an occasional white lie if it comes from a selfless place.

00:01:55.530 --> 00:02:00.110
But if you find your partner constantly telling you lies even over small matters,

00:02:00.420 --> 00:02:05.989
then it's time to re-evaluate how much you can trust them. A healthy relationship is built on honesty,

00:02:06.900 --> 00:02:08.900
understanding, and open communication,

00:02:09.209 --> 00:02:15.289
but your partner is only holding you back from going in that direct, but they choose not to tell you their true feelings and intentions.

00:02:15.900 --> 00:02:22.610
Three: Your partner love bombs you. Love bombing is a technique emotional manipulators use to get what they want.

00:02:22.860 --> 00:02:27.080
It involves offering you intense attention and bombarding you with many compliments.

00:02:27.269 --> 00:02:32.659
When your partner tries to win your heart over, they will purposely put you on a pedestal to make you feel reliant on them.

00:02:32.970 --> 00:02:37.549
They do this so they can be your only source you go to that makes you feel good about yourself.

00:02:38.250 --> 00:02:41.269
But this dangerously develops into a codependent relationship.

00:02:41.879 --> 00:02:43.939
That makes it toxic for the both of you.

00:02:44.190 --> 00:02:50.029
In fact, we even made a video on the different types of emotional manipulation that you can check out later.

00:02:50.819 --> 00:02:53.839
Four: Your partner frequently monitors you.

00:02:54.450 --> 00:02:57.829
Checking in is important to make sure you and your partner are on the same page,

00:02:58.230 --> 00:03:03.649
but if your partner is constantly bugging you, then they are stepping over the line and invading your sense of privacy.

00:03:04.650 --> 00:03:09.319
Examples of frequent monitoring include asking to see your text messages, phone calls, and emails and

00:03:09.840 --> 00:03:13.789
constantly calling or texting you throughout the day ask where you are or what you're up to.

00:03:14.430 --> 00:03:17.750
This stems from insecurity and a need for them to feel in control,

00:03:18.299 --> 00:03:21.828
which leaves you very little room to breathe and have a life outside of your relationship,

00:03:22.260 --> 00:03:25.220
which is important to have in order to maintain your individuality.

