00:03:42.060 --> 00:03:47.359
Five: Your partner isolates you. If you always feel like you need to ask for permission

00:03:47.609 --> 00:03:52.579
before attending events with friends or to hang out with family, then your partner may be possessive.

00:03:53.010 --> 00:03:58.549
Although it's sweet if your partner is protective of you, there's the difference between being caring versus being cleaned.

00:03:59.370 --> 00:04:03.620
Abusers have a tendency to isolate their partner to prevent others from helping them escape.

00:04:04.139 --> 00:04:07.819
They may also try to stir up drama between you and your family and friends

00:04:07.820 --> 00:04:12.880
so you no longer feel as close to them. This only helps them maintain their power and control over you.

00:04:13.520 --> 00:04:16.820
Six: Your partner blows hot and cold on you a lot.

00:04:17.660 --> 00:04:24.080
Abusers use the hot and cold technique in order to keep you on their leash. If your partner withdraws from you when upset them

00:04:24.080 --> 00:04:27.830
but comes running back to you at full speed after you've done something to make them happy,

00:04:27.960 --> 00:04:30.290
then this is their way of getting what they want.

00:04:30.660 --> 00:04:36.110
The hot and cold treatment acts as a reinforcement for you to behave by their own terms and regulations.

00:04:36.450 --> 00:04:38.719
This is how relationships turn into ownership

00:04:39.240 --> 00:04:41.240
instead of equal compromise.

00:04:41.640 --> 00:04:45.709
Seven: You constantly find yourself starting over with your partner.

00:04:46.470 --> 00:04:49.309
Fighting is normal and expected in any relationship,

00:04:49.470 --> 00:04:55.369
but if you have a common pattern of starting over with your partner frequently, then maybe it's time to examine why.

00:04:56.160 --> 00:05:01.610
Keeping up often has a negative connotation associated to it, but sometimes it's also the right choice.

00:05:02.130 --> 00:05:06.920
We usually hold on longer to something that's not working because we're afraid no one else will love us,

00:05:07.350 --> 00:05:10.969
but this is how your fears ruin your chances of finding something real.

00:05:11.430 --> 00:05:15.620
Love is always worth it if it means setting yourself free from the real people.

